                                                                                                                       7                                      Injury scare for Gambhir
            A STAFF REPORTER AMP; AGENCIES                      
	Calcutta/Chandigarh: Gautam Gambhir was hit on the right wrist by a rising delivery from Ben Hilfenhaus during Board Presidents XIs three-day match against Australia at the Sector 16 Stadium on Sunday.         
	The India opener was later taken to a nearby hospital where an X-ray and MRI confirmed that there was nothing to worry.         
	The MRI was all clear Theres nothing to worry. Hes fine, a Punjab Cricket Association (PCA) official told The Telegraph late on Sunday.         
	At the nearby PCA Stadium in Mohali, which is to host the first Test from Friday, Gambhirs opening partner Virender Sehwag was hit on the right knee by an Ishant Sharma delivery.         
	He immediately came off the ground and was given medical assistance.         
	Sehwag later played down the incident. Asked if the knee injury was serious, Sehwag smiled and asked, what knee?         
	The players had an exhaustive three-hour practice session at the PCA nets.         
	Sachin Tendulkar, VVS Laxman, Harbhajan Singh, Zaheer Khan, Ishant Sharma and Amit Mishra also sweated it out at the nets. Coach Gary Kirsten later said that he was pleased with the effort put in by the players.                                                                                                                     
